		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/06/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 08:01:35</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3296"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3296')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4620&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=A+Few+Ideas+%2D%2D+Opinions+Requested"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> First of all, I would like to offer my personal thanks (since I don't have the audacity to attempt to speak for everyone here, although I'm sure most share my sentiment) to Rich Waters.  He is very receptive and seems honestly concerned with addressing the problems facing Necromancers.  Thank you Rich, you're a glimmer of hope and the only reason I still have an everquest account.</P><P>  I know everyone is wrapped up with the new focus effects (or lack thereof), but I propose we think about something different and give Rich & crew a bit of time to work on them some.</P><P>  I have a couple of ideas I'd like everyone's feedback on (actually I have quite a few, but I'd rather keep this as short as possible).</P><P>  The first idea deals specifically with necro desirability in groups.  What about a targeted version of lich?  Maybe even a group version at higher levels?  In my opinion, I'd be ecstatic if this replaced the mana transfer line of spells.  Obviously, mana cost, duration, conversion rate, etc would all need to be adjusted for something like this to work, but I think it would go a long way to making necros desirable in groups, and the image of a group of skeletons cackling brings a tear to my eye.  The major drawback I foresee to something like this is a certain degree of animosity from enchanters.  Enchanters provide far more than mana regeneration though, and with KEI being the mana regen buff of choice, I see the impact as negligible.  Especially considering the duration of lich (and the HP loss), KEI/Clarity would still be very desirable in many situations.  This would also have a side effect of making cleric's line of group heals much more useful.</P><P>  My second idea deals mainly with the issue of pet health/resists in raid situations.  Why not have any beneficial buff cast on the pet's owner automatically stick to the pet as well?  This seems like it would resolve a large part of the pet survivability problem during raids while having very little impact on the solo necro.  And that would even be optional, depending on whether self-only buffs like our shielding line is allowed to stick to the pet.</P><P>  I'm really interested in hearing everyone's opinions of these ideas, perhaps theres flaws in my thinking that I overlooked.  Thanks for taking the time to read this.</P><P>Vaeaan</P><P> </font></td>

