        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Firstly, i dont want a targetable buff for anyone.  Its not why i play this class, and if i feel like going insane with requests, i log on my chanter and play him for a bit.  If VI did this, we would need substantial improvements in our mana regen to reset the gap between the classes.</P><P>The pet buff idea is a nice one, but frankly, there are bigger things to worry about.  Yes i'd love to see it, but no i'm not going to get overly supportive of it when we're seeing issues with dot stacking, mana regen (of other classes), dot vs dd issues existing.</P><P>If we want to make necro's desireable in groups, there are two ways to do it as i see it.  First is to further increase our dps, to a point where we can provide comperable melee dmg to lets say a war or ranger without consistently running oom.  Secondly, if VI gave us some screaming terror upgrades, one for a longer duration, and one that was similar to gok - with regards to mezzing higher lvl creatures.  This would reduce the reliance on needing chanters in groups, especially when a necro + shammy combo is present.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><br><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a><br> <BR>Innoruuk Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
