         Perhaps my ideas are simply stupid, but allow me to clarify a bit.  I wasn't thinking of it as a buff like clarity that people would bug you for.  Lich is extremely short duration, compared to Clarity, and especially compared to KEI.  I was thinking more along the lines of a group only buff (if it weren't, imagine running around randomly lich'ing level 1's).  I'd consider it a replacement to our mana transfer line (which I personally despise).  I don't know about the rest of you, but I'd much rather turn a group into a bunch of skeletons and give them tons of mana than twitch all my mana away.</P><P>I wholeheartedly agree that we need a damage upgrade, but guess what, a very vocal majority considers our solo ability overpowering as it stands right now.  Chances are we're going to get a ton of resistance to anything that would increase our ability to solo.  The targeted lich would basically remove any need for us to twitch anyone, and would make us highly desireable in groups (better mana regen than C3!).</P><P>Maybe it's different for the rest of you, but on my server necros are mostly unwanted in 50+ xp groups (I remember sitting in karnors for 6 hours lfg when I hit 53).  And on the only raid I've been on with a semi-uber guild, I got nothing but tells from wizzies during the entire thing saying "mana plz".  I didn't start a necro to just be a mana battery.  Our mana transfer spell line is inefficient and at least to me, degrading.  Maybe I'm crazy, but casting a group lich (which I'd be casting on myself anyhow) seems far more appealing than twitching.</P><P>Sure, an upgrade to ST would be great, so would the improved FD, but neither of those would really affect our group desirability.  Why get a necro to mez when you can get an enchanter who'll do it an order of magnitude better (and if you think they'd ever give necros anything like GoK or even Dazzle, you need to put the pipe down).</P><P>I thought of these ideas in the context of strictly helping our groupability while having a negligible impact on our solo ability, since that seems to be the underlying theme with necro enhancements.  This is a totally seperate issue from caster balancing, which is supposedly in the works.  This has to do with group desirability, something we sorely need.  Sure more DPS would help tons, but I seriously doubt we'll ever get to the point where a necro is wanted more than a rogue strictly based on damage.  I think that within itself is wrong, but EQ is a melee-centric game, like it or not.</P><P>Personally I'd just like to eventually get some higher end items (and for me, thats velious quest armor).  I won't be a twitch whore, so I don't go on raids, I haven't had a real group since level 51, and I'm getting tired of root cooking Katta guards.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

