        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Level up...find friends...join a guild.</P><P>About numero uno...giving people a lich type buff.  We can do that sorta.  It is called MindWrack.  It is the equivalent of giving the casters in your group 30 mana regen per tick if you cast it once per minute.  Level to 58 and then see how you like it.</P><P>Numero dos...this will help pets last longer on AE mobs...which I think is the primary complaint about high-end pets now.  I have heard this concept and I am indifferent as to how Verant decides to allow pets to take less damage from AE.  Just give us something that works reliably.</P><P>Finally, if you were on a large raid where you could not land any spells, then you may as well be a twitch whore.  Being a twitch whore seems pretty dependent on your server and the attitudes of people on that server.  But if you are in your low to mid 50's and go on a raid where the mob is 63+, good luck landing anything on it.  In order to get the cool gear, you need a guild.  You may have to twitch to win over the guild and gain enough of their attention and respect to educate them on how bad twitching is.  But most people will listen if you do it in a diplomatic way.  But if you get indignant and insult them...expect to solo to 60.  Patience young grasshopper...</P><P>Also, as you may have figured out...you can only stand one spot for so long.  There are plenty of places to make experience.  If you are without epic, using your pet will be way more efficient than root cooking and provides more variance...in my experience.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157918" target=new>Ishtarra Gemeinseele </a><BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
